TY  - JOUR
AU  - Foster, F. Douglas
AU  - Viswanathan, S.
T1  - A Theory of the Interday Variations in Volume, Variance, and Trading Costs in Securities Markets
PY  - 1990
Y1  - 1990/10/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/3.4.593
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 3
IS  - 4
SP  - 593
EP  - 624
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - In an adverse selection model of a securities market with one informed trader and several liquidity traders, we study the implications of the assumption that the informed trader has more information on Monday than on other days. We examine the interday variations in volume, variance, and adverse selection costs, and find that on monday the trading costs and the variance of price changes are highest, and the volume is lower than on Tuesday. These effects are stronger for firms with better public reporting and for firms with more discretionary liquidity trading.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/3.4.593
ER  - 



