T1  - Pricing Interest-Rate-Derivative Securities
PY  - 1990
Y1  - 1990/10/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/3.4.573
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 3
IS  - 4
SP  - 573
EP  - 592
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - This article shows that the one-state-variable interest-rate models of Vasicek (1977) and Cox, Ingersoll, and Ross (1985b) can be extended so that they are consistent with both the current term structure of interest rates and either the current volatilities of all spot interest rates or the current volatilities of all forward interest rates. The extended Vasicek model is shown to be very tractable analytically. The article compares option prices obtained using the extended Vasicek model with those obtained using a number of other models.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/3.4.573
ER  - 



